</div>

<a name="45-managed-access"></a>
<div class="problem-heading">Interstate 45 Northbound Managed Lanes: Insufficent Access from Downtown</div>
<div class="textblock">
    <div class="problem-solution">Problem</div>
    <ul>
        <li>There is only <span class="bold">ONE</span> access point to the northbound managed lanes in the downtown area, from Travis Street downtown</li>
        <li>Traffic on the northbound I-45 main lanes and coming from the downtown spur cannot get on the managed lanes to avoid the bottleneck at North Main</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="problem-solution">Potential Solution</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Add access to the northbound managed lanes from the I-45 main lanes and from the downtown spur</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="itemStatus">July and September 2015 Preliminary Status: This is being fixed, but I don't have exact details on how this will work. </div>
    <div class="itemStatusText">
        My view is that the regular northbound lanes should have an entrance to the northbound managed lanes BEFORE the point where backups are likely to occur. That means the entrance ramp should be as far south as possible. It appears that the location of the northbound
        entrance ramp is still under study and could be further north.

    </div>


