<a name="allen-parkway"></a>
<div class="problem-heading">Downtown Spur: Missing northbound access from Allen Parkway and no access to Memorial</div>
<div class="textblock">
    <div class="problem-solution">Problem</div>
    <ul>
        <li>There is a southbound exit to Allen Parkway, but no northbound on-ramp</li>
        <li>Allen Parkway traffic must make a detour to Bagby or Brazos to get on the spur, contributing to traffic congestion on those streets</li>
        <li>There are no connections to Memorial.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="problem-solution">Potential Solution</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Add a new ramp to the northbound spur to serve Allen Parkway</li>
        <li>Add two connection ramps at Memorial as shown on the map below</li>
    </ul>

    <div>Currently there are no connections at Memorial, but we need to think of the future. With increasing density and population along Buffalo Bayou and Washington Avenue, the Memorial connections will be needed to serve the growing population.</div>

    <div class="itemStatus">July and September 2015 Preliminary Status: Allen Parkway on-ramp will be added, no connections to Memorial</div>
    <div class="itemStatusText">
        As of July, a loop ramp from eastbound Allen Parkway to the northbound downtown spur was under study. As of September, they are now looking at more options, including adding a northbound ramp from West Dallas and using this ramp for eastbound Allen Parkway traffic, which would be a slightly longer connection path.
        I think ramp at West Dallas will work, especially since it has the potential to provide other benefits.

        <p>
            In a related development, the configuration of the downtown spur main lanes and adjacent Heiner street is under review and could be changed to a more conventional frontage road configuration, in contrast to the side-by-side design in the current schematic.
        </p>
        <p>
        No connections will be provided between Memorial and the downtown spur. The City of Houston is against connections at Memorial, and TxDOT also wants to avoid connections due to space issues and complications introduced by ramps. 
            This is disappointing because Memorial is great for reaching downtown, but it is mostly useless for going anywhere else. The addition of connections at the downtown spur would make Memorial much more useful.
            </p>
    </div>
</div>

